intelligence) agents make decisions, enhancing our understanding of their behavior.<br>\n<br>\n<strong>Your task: <\/strong><br>\nYou will review multiple scenarios where an AI model (referred to as the \u201cagent\u201d) makes decisions. Your task is to analyze these scenarios to understand the agent\u2019s decision-making process.<br>\n<br>\n<strong>The MiniGrid unlock environment:<\/strong>\n<ul>\n\t<li>The agent is represented as a red triangle.<\/li>\n\t<li>The primary objective is for the agent to retrieve the key and then open the door using the least number of steps possible.<\/li>\n\t<li>The agent\u2019s available actions include turning right, turning left, moving forward, picking up objects, and toggling (interacting with) objects.<\/li>\n\t<li>For instance, in the image below, the agent should take the fewest possible steps to reach the key, and then proceed with the minimum number of steps to the door to open it.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<div><img style=\"width: 608px; height: 320px;\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_ezzke4L4GCrIKLY\"><\/div>\n\n<div><br>\n<strong>How the agent works:<\/strong><\/div>\n\n<div>The AI agent is trained to solve the problem using a method called \u201creinforcement learning\u201d (RL), where the agent explores the grid and receives a positive reward for achieving its goal.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>The agent tries to learn how to maximize its total reward across different scenarios. Each scenario is also called an \u201cepisode\u201d, where in each episode the key and door locations change.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>Note that the training of the agent may not be perfect, so it may not always act optimally.<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Study Instructions: Objective: This study aims to evaluate various methods that explain how AI (a...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":1,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Our goal is to improve the collaboration between artificial-intelligence (AI) agents and humans.&nbsp;<div><br><\/div><div>In this study, you will be introduced to a game. The goal is to gain the most points in the game. To assist you, we will give you access to an agent that we have trained for the game.&nbsp;<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The experiment has two parts:&nbsp;<\/div><div>Part A: participants will query the AI agent about its behavior.&nbsp;<\/div><div>Part B (which will not take place today): participants will play the game in collaboration with the AI agent.&nbsp;<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>&nbsp;In this study, you will be asked to query an artificial-intelligence (AI) agent about its behavior using a system we have developed.&nbsp;<br><\/div>","DataExportTag":"instructions","QuestionID":"QID1212517608","QuestionJS":false}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517609","SecondaryAttribute":"The Settings - Highway:\u00a0 \u00a0 Cars are represented as green and blue rectangles moving along the hig.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The Settings - Highway:&nbsp;<\/b>\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>Cars are represented as green and blue rectangles moving along the highway lanes. <b>The AI agent control the <span style=\"color:#2ecc71;\">green<\/span> car<\/b>. The car can accelerate, decelerate, and change lanes.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div><img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_d0a2oxFoxCzZ70y\"><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>When any two cars collide, the two cars turn <strong><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\">red<\/span><\/strong> and gradually slow to a stop, as shown below.<br>\n<br>\n<img height=\"142\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_d10MYLnJtubciDc\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 142px;\" width=\"650\"><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The Settings - Highway:\u00a0 \u00a0 Cars are represented as green and blue rectangles moving along the hig...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>Game 1: The highway game:&nbsp;<\/b>\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>Cars are represented as green and blue rectangles moving along the highway lanes. <b>The AI agent control the <span style=\"color:#2ecc71;\">green<\/span> car.<\/b> Your goal is to drive safely. The car can accelerate, decelerate, and change lanes.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div><img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_d0a2oxFoxCzZ70y\" \/><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>When any two cars collide, points are deducted; the two cars turn <strong><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\">red<\/span><\/strong> and gradually slow to a stop, as shown below.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<img height=\"142\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_d10MYLnJtubciDc\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 142px;\" width=\"650\" \/><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q3","QuestionID":"QID1212517609"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517610","SecondaryAttribute":"Instructions In this study, you will be asked to identify a specific driver out of several potent...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<u><strong>Instructions<\/strong><\/u><br>\nIn this study, you will be asked to identify a specific driver out of several potential drivers, based on driving style.<br>\n<br>\nThe experiment contains 3 identical sections, each consists of 2 steps:<br>\n<br>\nStep 1: you will watch a short video of the driver in action (referred to as \"<strong>summary<\/strong>\").<br>\n<br>\nStep 2: you will answer a series of questions. On each, you will watch 3 shorter videos, each of a different driver, and will have to decide which of them is the driver from step 1.<br>\n<br>\nExample of a short video of a driver:<br>\n<video class=\"qmedia\" controls=\"true\" height=\"150\" preload=\"auto\" width=\"600\"><source src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/File.php?F=F_DORQIUfk881pHWy\" type=\"video\/mp4\"><embed align=\"middle\" autoplay=\"false\" bgcolor=\"white\" class=\"qmedia\" controller=\"true\" height=\"150\" pluginspage=\"http:\/\/www.apple.com\/quicktime\/download\/\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/File.php?F=F_DORQIUfk881pHWy\" type=\"video\/quicktime\" width=\"600\"><\/video><br><br>\nQuiz: Which car does the driver control?","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Instructions In this study, you will be asked to identify a specific driver out of several potent...","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Red car."},"2":{"Display":"Green car."},"3":{"Display":"Blue car."}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"CustomValidation","CustomValidation":{"Logic":{"0":{"0":{"ChoiceLocator":"q:\/\/QID1212517610\/SelectableChoice\/2","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">In this study, you will be asked to identify a specific driver out of a few driver.\nThe experiment has 3 identical sections, each consists of 2 steps: Step 1: you will watch a short video of the dr...<\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">Green car.<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Selected<\/span> ","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID1212517610\/SelectableChoice\/2","LogicType":"Question","Operator":"Selected","QuestionID":"QID1212517610","QuestionIDFromLocator":"QID1212517610","QuestionIsInLoop":"no","Type":"Expression"},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression"},"Message":{"description":"Wrong answer","libraryID":"UR_81haFOwirdOynSR","messageID":"MS_6nXUHGVMFeT5Fat","subMessageID":"VE_CUSTOM_VALIDATION_0"}}}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Quiz: Which car does the agent control?","DataExportTag":"Q4","QuestionID":"QID1212517610","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionJS":false}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517611","SecondaryAttribute":"Training AI agents: \u00a0 Roughly, AI agents are trained similarly to how a human would learn how to...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Training AI agents:<\/b>\n<div>&nbsp;\n<div>Roughly, AI agents are trained similarly to how a human would learn how to play a new game: they randomly try out actions. Actions lead to rewards (or penalties). Slowly and after many tries, the agent learns how to choose actions that maximize rewards (or minimize penalties).&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>In the highway game, the agent received a penalty whenever the green car collided with a blue car. It thus learned that crashing is counter-productive, and as a result, it learned how to drive safely.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div><b>Training is not perfect<\/b>. Scenarios that appear rarely or not at all in training lead to sub-optimal agent behavior. Also, the agent might not have enough training time to explore all the possible behaviors to learn the best one.<\/div><div>For example, in the highway game, the agent might learn to keep a safe distance from cars. But, if a car breaking unexpectedly or a high-speeding car have not appeared in training, it might not know how to take the necessary precautions to avoid them.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>Here's an example video of an agent driving in the highway environment. As you can see, this agent is not behaving optimally and collides with another car.<\/div>\n\n<div>\n<video class=\"qmedia\" controls=\"true\" height=\"150\" preload=\"auto\" width=\"600\"><source src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/File.php?F=F_8oIn0wLzZHnfO86\" type=\"video\/mp4\"><\/video>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Training AI agents: \u00a0 Roughly, AI agents are trained similarly to how a human would learn how to...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>Training AI agents:<\/b>\n<div>&nbsp;\n<div>Roughly, AI agents are trained similarly to how a human would learn how to play a new game: they randomly try out actions. Actions lead to rewards (or penalties). Slowly and after many tries, the agent learns how to choose actions that maximize rewards (or minimize penalties).&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>In the highway game, the agent received a penalty whenever the green car collided with a blue car. It thus learned that crashing is counter-productive, and as a result, it learned how to drive safely.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div><b>Training is not perfect<\/b>. Scenarios that appear rarely or not at all in training lead to sub-optimal agent behavior. Also, the agent might not have enough training time to explore all the possible behaviors to learn the best one.<\/div><div>For example, in the highway game, the agent might learn to keep a safe distance from cars. But, if a car breaking unexpectedly or a high-speeding car have not appeared in training, it might not know how to take the necessary precautions to avoid them.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>Here's an example video of an agent driving in the highway environment. As you can see, this agent is not behaving optimally and collides with another car.<\/div>\n\n<div>\n<video class=\"qmedia\" controls=\"true\" height=\"150\" preload=\"auto\" width=\"600\"><source src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/File.php?F=F_8oIn0wLzZHnfO86\" type=\"video\/mp4\"><\/video>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q5","QuestionID":"QID1212517611"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517612","SecondaryAttribute":"Quiz: Check ALL\u00a0that apply:\u00a0What can we learn from the above video?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Quiz:<br>Check <b>ALL<\/b>&nbsp;that apply:&nbsp;What can we learn from the above video?","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"MAVR","SubSelector":"TX","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Quiz: Check ALL\u00a0that apply:\u00a0What can we learn from the above video?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"The agent does not keep a safe distance."},"2":{"Display":"The agent is not properly trained to avoid collisions."},"5":{"Display":"The agent behaves optimally."},"6":{"Display":"The agent is rewarded for colliding with other cars."}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","5","2","6"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"CustomValidation","MinChoices":"1","CustomValidation":{"Logic":{"0":{"0":{"QuestionID":"QID1212517612","QuestionIsInLoop":"no","ChoiceLocator":"q:\/\/QID1212517612\/SelectableChoice\/1","Operator":"Selected","QuestionIDFromLocator":"QID1212517612","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID1212517612\/SelectableChoice\/1","Type":"Expression","LogicType":"Question","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">Quiz: Check ALL&nbsp;that apply:&nbsp;What can we learn from the above video?<\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">The agent does not keep a safe distance.<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Selected<\/span> "},"1":{"QuestionID":"QID1212517612","QuestionIsInLoop":"no","ChoiceLocator":"q:\/\/QID1212517612\/SelectableChoice\/2","Operator":"Selected","QuestionIDFromLocator":"QID1212517612","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID1212517612\/SelectableChoice\/2","Type":"Expression","LogicType":"Question","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">And<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">Quiz: Check ALL&nbsp;that apply:&nbsp;What can we learn from the above video?<\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">The agent is not properly trained to avoid collisions.<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Selected<\/span> ","Conjuction":"And"},"2":{"QuestionID":"QID1212517612","QuestionIsInLoop":"no","ChoiceLocator":"q:\/\/QID1212517612\/SelectedChoicesCount","Operator":"EqualTo","QuestionIDFromLocator":"QID1212517612","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID1212517612\/SelectedChoicesCount","RightOperand":"2","Type":"Expression","LogicType":"Question","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">And<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">Quiz: Check ALL&nbsp;that apply:&nbsp;What can we learn from the above video?<\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">q:\/\/QID361\/SelectedChoicesCount<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Equal to<\/span> <span class=\"RightOpDesc\"> 2 <\/span>","Conjuction":"And"},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression"},"Message":{"messageID":"MS_6nXUHGVMFeT5Fat","subMessageID":"VE_CUSTOM_VALIDATION_0","libraryID":"UR_81haFOwirdOynSR","description":"Wrong answer"}}}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Quiz:<br>Check <b>ALL<\/b>&nbsp;that apply:&nbsp;What can we learn from the above video?","DataExportTag":"Q6","QuestionID":"QID1212517612"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517613","SecondaryAttribute":"Explaining the agent\u2019s behavior: \u00a0 To help people understand the capabilities and limitations of.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Explaining the agent&rsquo;s behavior:<\/b>\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>To help people understand the capabilities and limitations of an agent, we developed a system that allows users to ask for examples of how the agent behaves based on previous interactions of the agent with the environment.<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Your task<\/strong> will be to ask the system for examples that interest you.<br \/>\nThe system will provide you with videos showing the agent behaving in the examples you specified.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n&nbsp;We hope that these videos will help you understand the agent&rsquo;s capabilities and strategy.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Explaining the agent\u2019s behavior: \u00a0 To help people understand the capabilities and limitations of...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>Explaining the agent&rsquo;s behavior:<\/b>\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>To help people understand the capabilities and limitations of an agent, we developed a system that allows users to ask for examples of how the agent behaves based on previous interactions of the agent with the environment.<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Your task<\/strong> will be to ask the system for examples that interest you.<br \/>\nThe system will provide you with videos showing the agent behaving in the examples you specified.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n&nbsp;We hope that these videos will help you understand the agent&rsquo;s capabilities and strategy.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q7","QuestionID":"QID1212517613"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517614","SecondaryAttribute":"How to ask the system: Our systems outputs videos of the agent driving on the highway. You can sp...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><b>How to ask the system:<\/b><br \/>\nOur systems outputs videos of the agent driving on the highway. You can specify which videos you&rsquo;d like to see.<br \/>\nTo do so, you will need to provide a description of the first (&quot;start&quot;) and last (&quot;end&quot;) frames of the video that you are interested in.<br \/>\nThis is done using dropdowns.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nYou can specify the following:<\/p>\n\n<ul dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<li><strong>Position<\/strong>: Agent&#39;s position compared to other cars.\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>options<\/strong>: behind, in front of, above, below.<br \/>\n\t\t<br \/>\n\t\t&nbsp;<\/li>\n\t<\/ul>\n\t<\/li>\n\t<li><strong>Lane<\/strong>: Which lane the agent is in\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>options<\/strong>: lane 1, lane 2, lane 3, lane 4.<\/li>\n\t<\/ul>\n\t<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Example:<\/strong><br \/>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_efmERyFo92Qvsi2\" style=\"width: 373px; height: 64px;\" \/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img height=\"100\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_5axLFSGmjByKQiq\" style=\"width: 168px; height: 100px;\" width=\"168\" \/><br \/>\n<br \/>\nThese specifications are <strong>optional<\/strong>, however if you do not choose, the system can output videos with any of the possible options.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"How to ask the system: Our systems outputs videos of the agent driving on the highway. You can sp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<p dir=\"ltr\"><b>How to ask the system:<\/b><br \/>\nOur systems outputs videos of the agent driving on the highway. You can specify which videos you&rsquo;d like to see.<br \/>\nTo do so, you will need to provide a description of the first (&quot;start&quot;) and last (&quot;end&quot;) frames of the video that you are interested in.<br \/>\nThis is done using dropdowns.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nYou can specify the following:<\/p>\n\n<ul dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<li><strong>Position<\/strong>: Agent&#39;s position compared to other cars.\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>options<\/strong>: behind, in front of, above, below.<br \/>\n\t\t<br \/>\n\t\t&nbsp;<\/li>\n\t<\/ul>\n\t<\/li>\n\t<li><strong>Lane<\/strong>: Which lane the agent is in\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>options<\/strong>: lane 1, lane 2, lane 3, lane 4.<\/li>\n\t<\/ul>\n\t<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Example:<\/strong><br \/>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_efmERyFo92Qvsi2\" style=\"width: 373px; height: 64px;\" \/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img height=\"100\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_5axLFSGmjByKQiq\" style=\"width: 168px; height: 100px;\" width=\"168\" \/><br \/>\n<br \/>\nThese specifications are <strong>optional<\/strong>, however if you do not choose, the system can output videos with any of the possible options.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>","DataExportTag":"Q8","QuestionID":"QID1212517614"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517615","SecondaryAttribute":"Additional clarifications 1)\u00a0Lanes are numbered from top to bottom\u00a0(i.e. lane 1 is always the top.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<h4><strong>Additional clarifications<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n<div><strong>1)&nbsp;<\/strong><b>Lanes<\/b> are numbered from <b>top to bottom&nbsp;<\/b>(i.e. lane 1 is always the topmost lane.)<br>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_cSgdLQXNZwjxpk2\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 175px;\"><\/div><div><br><\/div>\n\n<div><strong>2) Positions above\/below<\/strong> refer to <b>all<\/b> lanes between the agent and the other car<strong>.<\/strong><br>\nExample: Agent (Lane 4) below car (Lane 1)<br>\n<img height=\"172\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_6XQFD8Y73i7em7s\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 172px;\" width=\"200\"><br>\n<br>\n<strong>3) Positions behind\/In <\/strong><b>front of<\/b> refer to a set distance between the agent and the other car<strong>:<\/strong><\/div>\n\n<div>Example: <strong>In front of<\/strong><br>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_bdcx1HJzxh9U8Ye\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 149px;\"><br>\n<strong>Not in front of:<\/strong><br>\n<img height=\"145\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_39k4nOYiX16tasu\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 145px;\" width=\"230\"><\/div>","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Additional clarifications 1)\u00a0Lanes are numbered from top to bottom\u00a0(i.e. lane 1 is always the top...","Choices":[],"ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<h4><strong>Additional clarifications<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n<div><strong>1)&nbsp;<\/strong><b>Lanes<\/b> are numbered from <b>top to bottom&nbsp;<\/b>(i.e. lane 1 is always the topmost lane.)<br>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_cSgdLQXNZwjxpk2\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 175px;\"><\/div><div><br><\/div>\n\n<div><strong>2) Positions above\/below<\/strong> refer to <b>all<\/b> lanes between the agent and the other car<strong>.<\/strong><br>\nExample: Agent (Lane 4) below car (Lane 1)<br>\n<img height=\"172\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_6XQFD8Y73i7em7s\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 172px;\" width=\"200\"><br>\n<br>\n<strong>3) Positions behind\/In <\/strong><b>front of<\/b> refer to a set distance between the agent and the other car<strong>:<\/strong><\/div>\n\n<div>Example: <strong>In front of<\/strong><br>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_bdcx1HJzxh9U8Ye\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 149px;\"><br>\n<strong>Not in front of:<\/strong><br>\n<img height=\"145\" src=\"https:\/\/technioniit.eu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_39k4nOYiX16tasu\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 145px;\" width=\"230\"><\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q9","QuestionID":"QID1212517615"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9RXvoU2Xl9xbrf0","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1212517616","SecondaryAttribute":"Example of frame description using dropdowns: Note: when specifying the \"End Frame\" another \"Posi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Example of frame description using dropdowns:\n<div><span style=\"font-size:13px;\"><strong>Note: when specifying the \"End Frame\" another \"Position = Collision\" is also available.<\/strong><\/span><\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DD","Selector":"DL","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","VariableCount":2},"QuestionDescription":"Example of frame description using dropdowns: Note: when specifying the \"End Frame\" another \"Posi...","Choices":{"2":{"Display":"Position"},"3":{"Display":"Lane"}},"ChoiceOrder":["2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"Answers":{"1":{"Display":"-----"},"2":{"Display":"----- ~ -----"},"3":{"Display":"----- ~ Lane 1"},"4":{"Display":"----- ~ Lane 2"},"5":{"Display":"----- ~ Lane 3"},"6":{"Display":"----- ~ Lane 4"},"7":{"Display":"Behind"},"8":{"Display":"Behind ~ -----"},"9":{"Display":